\\documentclass.name: \documentclass
\\documentclass.description: Specifies the overall layout of the document by selecting a document class and optional parameters

\\documentstyle.name: \documentstyle
\\documentstyle.description: Specifies the overall layout of the document by selecting a document style and optional parameters. This command is for LaTeX 2.09 and deprecated in favor of \documentclass.

\\usepackage.name: \usepackage
\\usepackage.description: Loads a LaTeX package with optional parameters

\\maketitle.name: \maketitle
\\maketitle.description: Generates the title block using information from \title, \author, \date, and \thanks

\\title.name: \title
\\title.description: Defines the document title to be typeset by \maketitle

\\author.name: \author
\\author.description: Defines the document author(s) to be typeset by \maketitle

\\date.name: \date
\\date.description: Defines the document date to be typeset by \maketitle

\\thanks.name: \thanks
\\thanks.description: Provides a footnote for the title, author, or date in the title block

\\part.name: \part
\\part.description: Starts a major sectional division at the part level; typically used in book classes; optionally adds an entry to the table of contents

\\part*.name: \part*
\\part*.description: Starts a major sectional division at the part level without adding an entry to the table of contents

\\chapter.name: \chapter
\\chapter.description: Starts a major sectional division at the chapter level; typically used in book and report classes; optionally adds an entry to the table of contents

\\chapter*.name: \chapter*
\\chapter*.description: Starts a major sectional division at the chapter level without adding an entry to the table of contents

\\section.name: \section
\\section.description: Starts a major sectional division at the section level; typically used in articles, books, and reports; optionally adds an entry to the table of contents

\\section*.name: \section*
\\section*.description: Starts a major sectional division at the section level without adding an entry to the table of contents

\\subsection.name: \subsection
\\subsection.description: Starts a sectional division at the subsection level; optionally adds an entry to the table of contents

\\subsection*.name: \subsection*
\\subsection*.description: Starts a sectional division at the subsection level without adding an entry to the table of contents

\\subsubsection.name: \subsubsection
\\subsubsection.description: Starts a sectional division at the subsubsection level; optionally adds an entry to the table of contents

\\subsubsection*.name: \subsubsection*
\\subsubsection*.description: Starts a sectional division at the subsubsection level without adding an entry to the table of contents

\\paragraph.name: \paragraph
\\paragraph.description: Starts a sectional division at the paragraph level; optionally adds an entry to the table of contents

\\paragraph*.name: \paragraph*
\\paragraph*.description: Starts a sectional division at the paragraph level without adding an entry to the table of contents

\\subparagraph.name: \subparagraph
\\subparagraph.description: Starts a sectional division at the subparagraph level; optionally adds an entry to the table of contents

\\subparagraph*.name: \subparagraph*
\\subparagraph*.description: Starts a sectional division at the subparagraph level without adding an entry to the table of contents

\\leq.name: \leq
\\leq.description: less than or equal to sign

\\sqsubseteq.name: \sqsubseteq
\\sqsubseteq.description: square subset of or equal to

\\sqsupseteq.name: \sqsupseteq
\\sqsupseteq.description: square superset of or equal to

\\deg.name: \deg
\\deg.description: degree of a polynomial or vertex

\\pmod.name: \pmod
\\pmod.description: typesets the modulus in congruence relations, displaying (mod n) in math mode

\\bigl.name: \bigl
\\bigl.description: applies big sizing to left delimiter

\\bigr.name: \bigr
\\bigr.description: applies big sizing to right delimiter

\\Bigl.name: \Bigl
\\Bigl.description: applies Big sizing to left delimiter

\\Bigr.name: \Bigr
\\Bigr.description: applies Big sizing to right delimiter

\\biggl.name: \biggl
\\biggl.description: applies bigg sizing to left delimiter

\\biggr.name: \biggr
\\biggr.description: applies bigg sizing to right delimiter

\\Biggl.name: \Biggl
\\Biggl.description: applies Bigg sizing to left delimiter

\\Biggr.name: \Biggr
\\Biggr.description: applies Bigg sizing to right delimiter

\\bibliography.name: \bibliography
\\bibliography.description: specifies the bibliography database files to use

\\bibliographystyle.name: \bibliographystyle
\\bibliographystyle.description: specifies the bibliography style to use

\\bibitem.name: \bibitem
\\bibitem.description: creates a bibliography entry with optional label

\\cite.name: \cite
\\cite.description: cites one or more bibliography entries with optional prefix text

\\nocite.name: \nocite
\\nocite.description: includes bibliography entries in the bibliography without citing them in text

\\sffamily.name: \sffamily
\\sffamily.description: sets font family to sans serif

\\scshape.name: \scshape
\\scshape.description: sets font shape to small caps

\\textmd.name: \textmd
\\textmd.description: typesets text in medium (normal) weight font

\\textbf.name: \textbf
\\textbf.description: typesets text in bold weight font

\\textrm.name: \textrm
\\textrm.description: typesets text in roman (serif) font family

\\textsf.name: \textsf
\\textsf.description: typesets text in sans serif font family

\\texttt.name: \texttt
\\texttt.description: typesets text in typewriter (monospace) font family

\\textup.name: \textup
\\textup.description: typesets text in upright font shape

\\textit.name: \textit
\\textit.description: typesets text in italic font shape

\\textsl.name: \textsl
\\textsl.description: typesets text in slanted font shape

\\textsc.name: \textsc
\\textsc.description: typesets text in small caps font shape

\\textnormal.name: \textnormal
\\textnormal.description: typesets text in document default font

\\rm.name: \rm
\\rm.description: legacy: sets font family to roman (deprecated, use \rmfamily)

\\sf.name: \sf
\\sf.description: legacy: sets font family to sans serif (deprecated, use \sffamily)

\\tt.name: \tt
\\tt.description: legacy: sets font family to typewriter (deprecated, use \ttfamily)

\\bf.name: \bf
\\bf.description: legacy: sets font series to bold (deprecated, use \bfseries)

\\it.name: \it
\\it.description: legacy: sets font shape to italic (deprecated, use \itshape)

\\sl.name: \sl
\\sl.description: legacy: sets font shape to slanted (deprecated, use \slshape)

\\sc.name: \sc
\\sc.description: legacy: sets font shape to small caps (deprecated, use \scshape)

\\em.name: \em
\\em.description: legacy: emphasis font (contextual italic/upright, deprecated, use \emph{text})

\\cal.name: \cal
\\cal.description: legacy: calligraphic font for math mode (deprecated, use \mathcal{text})

\\mit.name: \mit
\\mit.description: legacy: math italic font for math mode (deprecated, use \mathit{text})

\\scriptsize.name: \scriptsize
\\scriptsize.description: sets font size to script size

\\footnotesize.name: \footnotesize
\\footnotesize.description: sets font size to footnote size

\\normalsize.name: \normalsize
\\normalsize.description: sets font size to normal size

\\centering.name: \centering
\\centering.description: centers subsequent text lines until the end of the current group or environment

\\raggedright.name: \raggedright
\\raggedright.description: left-aligns subsequent text lines, leaving right margin ragged

\\raggedleft.name: \raggedleft
\\raggedleft.description: right-aligns subsequent text lines, leaving left margin ragged
